simple BSM option pricer
usage:
  $ ./main C -s 100 -k 100 -r 0.05 -T 1 -v 0.10
or generally:
  $ ./main <C|P> -s <S₀> -k <K> -r <r> -T <T> -v <σ_total> 
with:
  <C|P>  call or put
  -s     initial stock price S_0
  -k     strike price K
  -r     risk-free rate r (annual, e.g. 0.05)
  -T     time to maturity T in years (e.g. 1.0)
  -v     total volatility over T (annualized, e.g. 0.2)
